# update-llm-connection.word — re-mint the changed fields of a being's llm connection
# (connect.js update path, materials/being/ops.js update-llm-connection DO op).
#
# ONE fact — the merged connection at qualities.llmConnections.<id>. A connection is one
# word however rich its content (name/url/model/key), the spacebar: create-matter is the
# proof. The host see resolve-connection-update is the floor — validate, SSRF-gate the new
# base URL, re-encrypt a new key, merge only the CHANGED fields — and lays NO fact; the
# dispatcher lays the one do:set-being (target = the being, skipAudit gone). encryptedApiKey
# rides as ciphertext (redact strips it). `wasAssigned` rides the return so the handler can
# bust the client cache post-fact (a side-effect, not a fact).
#
# The bridge binds `target` (the being), the update `params` (connectionId, name, baseUrl,
# model, apiKey), `caller` (the acting being), and `branch`.

When a being updates an llm connection:
  If no caller, refuse with "update-llm-connection requires an identified actor".
  see resolve-connection-update(target, params, caller, branch) as patch.
  Return connectionId: $patch.connectionId, wasAssigned: $patch.wasAssigned, factParams: $patch.setBeingParams.
